text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia acoma is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Great Southern and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The erect, spreading and spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.1 to 0.6 metres (0 to 2 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
